T1	Intervention 658 1070	Forty patients were randomly assigned to receive either fentanyl (10 micrograms/mL) or a fentanyl/bupivacaine (0.1%) mixture epidurally corresponding to the dermatome of the surgical incision in a double-blind fashion for the first 18 hours after major abdominal surgery. The infusion was titrated for each patient to the rate required for pain relief during forced inspiration (pain score < or = 2, maximum 10).
